# crude

Full-stack monorepo: NestJS backend + React + Vite frontend. App title: **crude**.

## Stack
- **Backend**: NestJS 11, Express 5, TypeScript (ES2023, nodenext)
- **Frontend**: React 19, Vite 7, TypeScript (ES2022, bundler, react-jsx)
- **Package manager**: `pnpm` — never npm/yarn

## Structure
- `server/` — NestJS source (main, app.module, app.controller, app.service, vite.middleware)
- `client/` — React source (main.tsx mounts to #root)
- `index.html` — loads `/client/main.tsx`; title "crude"
- `vite.config.ts` — alias `@` → project root; build outDir `dist/client`

## Key Conventions
- **API routes** must be prefixed with `/api` — ViteMiddleware passes `/api` to NestJS, everything else goes to Vite/static
- **Client alias**: `@/` → `./client/` (tsconfig.app.json, vite.config)
- **Prettier**: single quotes, trailing commas
- **Server ESLint**: `eslint.server.config.mjs` — type-checked via tsconfig.server.json
- **Client ESLint**: `eslint.client.config.js` — `components/ui/**` has react-refresh/only-export-components off

## Scripts
- `pnpm start:dev` — dev (Nest + Vite)
- `pnpm build` — nest build && vite build
- `pnpm start:prod` — node dist/server/main
- `pnpm lint` — lint:client then lint:server

## Technical
- ViteMiddleware: lazy init; dev = Vite dev server middleware; prod = static from dist/client + SPA fallback
- Server baseUrl `./server`; emits to `dist/server`
- Client `@/*` → `./client/*`
